Re: JSON-RPC password

Bitcointalk

2010-07-23 17:07:40 UTC - [11]Original Post

   [12]Quote from: gavinandresen on July 23, 2010, 03:11:45 PM
   Question for everybody:  should I add a section to the wiki page
   describing, in detail, how to do HTTP Basic authentication?  PHP and
   Python make is really easy-- just use the
   [13]http://user:pass@host:port/ URL syntax.
   Yes, I think that would be really good so each dev doesnʼt have to
   figure it out themselves.  We need a simple example for each of Python,
   PHP and Java importing the json-rpc library and using it to do a
   getinfo or something, including doing the http authentication part.
